A quick recap on SRE Site reliability engineering (SRE) is a discipline that incorporates aspects of software engineering and applies them to infrastructure and operations problems.[1] The main goals are to create scalable and highly reliable software systems. According to Ben Treynor, founder of Google&rsquo;s Site Reliability Team, SRE is &ldquo;what happens when a software engineer is tasked with what used to be called operations.&rdquo;
